g active stars, Neptune-mass planets around moderate\nrotators and that Super-Earths are only detectable around very slowly rotating\nstars. The effects of an increase in stellar activity jitter by observing\nyounger stars can be compensated for by extending the observational base-line\nto at least 100 epochs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Nov 2013 19:27:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
