ergy range of overlap with space-based\ninstruments (above about 40 GeV) is about one order of magnitude better with\nrespect to Fermi. This makes evident the constraining power of ground-based\nobservations and shows that the MAGIC telescope has reached the required\nperformance to make possible GRB multiwavelength studies in the very high\nenergy range.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Nov 2013 19:52:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-15"}
