s at\na fairly steady rate of 0.38e16 Mx/s over two days, while the radiated power\nvaries between 2~8e25 erg/s over the same time. We find that as much as 40% of\nthe total emerged flux at any given time may have reconnected. The total amount\nof transferred flux (1e21 Mx) and radiated energy (7.2e30 ergs) are comparable\nto that of a large M- or small X-class flare, but are stretched out over 45\nhours.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Nov 2013 00:34:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
